The paper deals with the cryptanalysis of a public key cryptosystem, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The attack is based on subcodes of algebraic geometry codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes, and thus the paper may also be relevant to coding theory (cs.CC). The proposed attack involves using the Schur product to distinguish between codes, which is a technique commonly used in algebraic complexity theory (cs.DS) and computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) as it deals with the analysis of codes used in communication systems.
